	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Of course many games did this. The ones I can think of right now are :<br />- Punch Out<br />- Door Door<br />- Donkey Kong<br />- Fire Emblem (both on maps and during battles)<br />- Mega Man games (minibosses like the Dragon of Dr. Wily 2)<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I remember finding one NES game, some vaguely action-adventurey thing, where the boss battles did this—they'd fade out the background, and scroll the boss around while using sprites for the player and everything else.<br /></div><br />Sounds like Blaster Master. However I think it handles background bosses in a very lame way as opposed to the games I mentionned above (it just fades the backgrounds and display the boss only, this is too easy and looks ugly).<br />Gradius games does this as well.<br /><br />Also you'd want to take a look at <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=22&amp;t=9549" class="postlink">this demo</a> I wrote some time ago.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


