	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Bucky O'Hare does lots of neat tricks with background tiles.<br /><br /><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dWHPNnrTmKs&amp;t=4m17s" class="postlink">This scene</a> combines bg-based enemies with parallax scrolling for example (and the boss throws rocks made of bg tiles). <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dWHPNnrTmKs&amp;t=14m28s" class="postlink">Here</a> the large green ball is part of the background (and the scene before that does parallax scrolling by rewriting bg tiles).<br /><br />And yeah, most of those are not unique to Bucky O'Hare (it seems to have borrowed a lot of stuff from Battletoads for example), but I can't think of any other game that uses so many different bg-based effects (Battletoads might be a contender).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


